'''Birdhana''' is a village in Jhajjar Mandal, Jhajjar District, Haryana State, India.<ref name="Swaminathan2005">{{cite book|author=Madhura Swaminathan|title=Financial liberalization and rural credit in India|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=HlEWAQAAMAAJ|date=1 January 2005|publisher=Tulika Books|isbn=978-81-85229-94-2}}</ref><ref>[http://www.thehindu.com/2005/02/06/stories/2005020610120500.htm "Other States - Haryana Repoll ordered"]. ''The Hindu''. </ref><ref name="Haryana1993">{{cite book|author=India. Director of Census Operations, Haryana|title=Census of India, 1991: A & B. General population tables and primary census abstract|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=x5gUAQAAMAAJ|year=1993|publisher=Govt. of Haryana}}</ref>

==Geography==
Birdhana is 5.6 km distance from its Mandal Main Town Jhajjar. Birdhana is 5.5 km distance from its District Main City Jhajjar and 230 km distance from its State Main City Chandigarh. 

Nearby villages are Mehrana(2.4 k.m.) ,Gudha(3.2 k.m.) ,Jondhi *(3.7 k.m.) ,Dujana(4 k.m.) ,Chamanpura(4.3 k.m.). Nearby towns are Jhajjar(5.6 k.m.), Beri(9.8 k.m.),Matannail(21 k.m.),Bahadurgarh(29.7 k.m.).

The Birdhana Pin Code is 124102. There are several nearby lakes.

==People==
Most of the population is of Dahiya Gotra, which comes under the Jat community. Farming is a common occupation in the village.   There are several temples and shrines with a long history.<ref name="Datta1999">{{cite book|author=Nonica Datta|title=Forming an Identity: A Social History of the Jats|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=sBBuAAAAMAAJ|year=1999|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=978-0-19-564719-8}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=gazetteer of the  karnal district|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=dpsIAAAAQAAJ|year=1883}}</ref>

